Well, so I was
surprised to find out

00:10:33.740 --> 00:10:36.230 align:middle line:84%
that the Federal Reserve
was the fourth attempt

00:10:36.230 --> 00:10:38.604 align:middle line:90%
to do that in the United States.

00:10:38.604 --> 00:10:40.020 align:middle line:84%
I was really
surprised to find out

00:10:40.020 --> 00:10:42.650 align:middle line:84%
that at the time of the
signing of the Declaration

00:10:42.650 --> 00:10:47.780 align:middle line:84%
of Independence and the writing
of the Constitution itself,

00:10:47.780 --> 00:10:50.690 align:middle line:84%
we already had
one of those here.

00:10:50.690 --> 00:10:53.440 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know it, but
there was one there.

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:56.450 align:middle line:90%
And it didn't last very long.

00:10:56.450 --> 00:10:58.200 align:middle line:84%
They were raising
money, by the way,

00:10:58.200 --> 00:10:59.740 align:middle line:84%
by printing it and
creating it out

00:10:59.740 --> 00:11:03.180 align:middle line:84%
of nothing to help finance
the Revolutionary War.

00:11:03.180 --> 00:11:05.920 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the reasons that
the politicians and the bankers

00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:07.650 align:middle line:84%
form this partnership,
is because it's

00:11:07.650 --> 00:11:10.270 align:middle line:90%
mutually advantageous.

00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:12.870 align:middle line:84%
The politicians are able
to get fast, easy money

00:11:12.870 --> 00:11:15.772 align:middle line:84%
in unlimited quantities, because
the banks just create it.

00:11:15.772 --> 00:11:16.480 align:middle line:90%
There's no limit.

00:11:16.480 --> 00:11:18.270 align:middle line:84%
It's not backed by
gold or anything.

00:11:18.270 --> 00:11:20.700 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why the
politicians like it.

00:11:20.700 --> 00:11:23.270 align:middle line:84%
And the bankers like it because,
heck, they created money,

00:11:23.270 --> 00:11:24.440 align:middle line:84%
and now they're
collecting interest

00:11:24.440 --> 00:11:25.570 align:middle line:90%
on this thing they created.

00:11:25.570 --> 00:11:26.650 align:middle line:90%
They like that.

00:11:26.650 --> 00:11:28.890 align:middle line:84%
And everybody likes it
except the poor suckers

00:11:28.890 --> 00:11:30.600 align:middle line:84%
out there like us
who have to pay

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:34.390 align:middle line:84%
the taxes in the form of either
direct taxes or inflation,

00:11:34.390 --> 00:11:36.620 align:middle line:84%
prices going up to
pay for all of this.

00:11:36.620 --> 00:11:40.070 align:middle line:84%
So that was already
in place at that time.

00:11:40.070 --> 00:11:42.960 align:middle line:84%
It had ruined what was left
of the economy at the end

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:44.790 align:middle line:90%
of the Revolutionary War.

00:11:44.790 --> 00:11:47.790 align:middle line:84%
And there was a strong
movement to get rid of it.

00:11:47.790 --> 00:11:48.600 align:middle line:90%
In fact, they did.

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:51.280 align:middle line:84%
Within a year or two-- I've
forgotten the exact time frame,

00:11:51.280 --> 00:11:55.060 align:middle line:84%
but very soon after the
creation of the country,

00:11:55.060 --> 00:11:57.690 align:middle line:84%
the first central bank
of the United States

00:11:57.690 --> 00:11:59.540 align:middle line:90%
was allowed to expire.

00:11:59.540 --> 00:12:02.520 align:middle line:84%
The charter expired,
and it became, I think,

00:12:02.520 --> 00:12:07.337 align:middle line:84%
a Philadelphia bank,
just a private bank.

00:12:07.337 --> 00:12:08.420 align:middle line:90%
The second one came along.

00:12:08.420 --> 00:12:11.310 align:middle line:84%
It was the First Bank
of the United States.

00:12:11.310 --> 00:12:13.510 align:middle line:90%
And it went out of business.

00:12:13.510 --> 00:12:14.560 align:middle line:90%
The third one came along.

00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:16.420 align:middle line:84%
It was the Third Bank
of the United States.

00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:17.920 align:middle line:84%
And that was the
one where there was

00:12:17.920 --> 00:12:24.110 align:middle line:84%
a great battle between President
Andrew Jackson and the bankers.

00:12:24.110 --> 00:12:26.530 align:middle line:90%
He's famous for that battle.

00:12:26.530 --> 00:12:29.960 align:middle line:10%
Even the history
books today, you

00:12:29.960 --> 00:12:33.140 align:middle line:10%
can find maybe a couple of lines
about Andrew Jackson's battle

00:12:33.140 --> 00:12:34.240 align:middle line:10%
against the bank.

00:12:34.240 --> 00:12:36.190 align:middle line:90%
You don't get any details.

00:12:36.190 --> 00:12:38.640 align:middle line:84%
All you know is that Jackson
was against the banks,

00:12:38.640 --> 00:12:40.931 align:middle line:84%
and you wonder, really, who
were the good guys in that,

00:12:40.931 --> 00:12:42.330 align:middle line:90%
maybe Jackson, maybe the banks.

00:12:42.330 --> 00:12:47.090 align:middle line:84%
But it turned out that Jackson
really based his career

00:12:47.090 --> 00:12:48.570 align:middle line:90%
on getting rid of the banks.

00:12:48.570 --> 00:12:51.020 align:middle line:84%
He called them,
you den of vipers!

00:12:51.020 --> 00:12:53.730 align:middle line:84%
That was his attack
phrase, colorful language

00:12:53.730 --> 00:12:56.370 align:middle line:84%
for a president speaking
against the central bank.

00:12:56.370 --> 00:12:59.730 align:middle line:90%
He says, I will cast thee out.

00:12:59.730 --> 00:13:01.480 align:middle line:84%
There was almost a
religious fervor.

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:04.020 align:middle line:84%
And he put his political
career on the line.

00:13:04.020 --> 00:13:08.960 align:middle line:84%
And he almost lost that
battle, because Nicholas Biddle

00:13:08.960 --> 00:13:11.680 align:middle line:84%
was the head of the
bank at that time.

00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:15.860 align:middle line:84%
And he is quoted as saying,
I will get this guy Jackson.

00:13:15.860 --> 00:13:17.400 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to ruin him.

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:18.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to have him impeached.

00:13:18.970 --> 00:13:23.760 align:middle line:84%
And he said, the
United States may fall,

00:13:23.760 --> 00:13:26.420 align:middle line:90%
but the bank will not fall.

00:13:26.420 --> 00:13:28.420 align:middle line:90%
He's quoted as saying that.

00:13:28.420 --> 00:13:32.740 align:middle line:84%
And so what he did is he
started to pull in loans that

00:13:32.740 --> 00:13:35.280 align:middle line:90%
were outstanding to businesses.

00:13:35.280 --> 00:13:36.710 align:middle line:90%
He was demanding full payment.

00:13:36.710 --> 00:13:38.640 align:middle line:84%
And it was putting
companies out of business.

00:13:38.640 --> 00:13:43.480 align:middle line:84%
He was deliberately creating
a man-made recession

00:13:43.480 --> 00:13:44.840 align:middle line:90%
so that he could say, you see?

00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:48.170 align:middle line:84%
That's Jackson's fault.
He talks about taking away

00:13:48.170 --> 00:13:51.330 align:middle line:84%
the power of our bank, and look
what he's doing to the economy.

00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:53.977 align:middle line:84%
And people were saying,
yeah, Jackson, you dirty guy.

00:13:53.977 --> 00:13:55.560 align:middle line:84%
Look what you're
doing to the economy.

00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:58.275 align:middle line:84%
And there was a movement
in Congress to impeach him.

00:13:58.275 --> 00:14:01.340 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turned out
that almost by accident,

00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:05.440 align:middle line:84%
there was one of the large
newspapers in the Midwest that

00:14:05.440 --> 00:14:08.810 align:middle line:84%
picked up on the fact that
Biddle was deliberately

00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:09.310 align:middle line:90%
doing this.

00:14:09.310 --> 00:14:10.580 align:middle line:90%
They published it.

00:14:10.580 --> 00:14:14.020 align:middle line:84%
And when the news hit
that it was Biddle himself

00:14:14.020 --> 00:14:17.210 align:middle line:84%
who was doing this, then
the tide of public opinion

00:14:17.210 --> 00:14:19.950 align:middle line:84%
turned, and it was Biddle
who found himself out

00:14:19.950 --> 00:14:22.400 align:middle line:84%
on the street, and
Jackson had the support,

00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:24.520 align:middle line:84%
and the bank was
finally terminated.

00:14:24.520 --> 00:14:28.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: What's your
perspective on the War of 1812?

00:14:28.030 --> 00:14:31.090 align:middle line:84%
America had declared its
independence from Britain.

00:14:31.090 --> 00:14:34.470 align:middle line:84%
But then the British come back,
and they tried to invade again.

00:14:34.470 --> 00:14:37.290 align:middle line:84%
Do you see that
historical event as being

00:14:37.290 --> 00:14:40.662 align:middle line:84%
significant in the research
that you've conducted?

00:14:40.662 --> 00:14:42.370 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: I'm not
one of the people that

00:14:42.370 --> 00:14:47.080 align:middle line:84%
is so concerned about foreign
involvement or influence

00:14:47.080 --> 00:14:48.840 align:middle line:90%
in our Federal Reserve system.

00:14:48.840 --> 00:14:50.460 align:middle line:90%
I know it's there.

00:14:50.460 --> 00:14:53.880 align:middle line:84%
I know that the Rothschilds and
the Warburgs in the beginning

00:14:53.880 --> 00:14:57.280 align:middle line:84%
were very influential in
the policies and so forth.

00:14:57.280 --> 00:15:01.510 align:middle line:84%
But I don't really see
that as a major factor.

00:15:01.510 --> 00:15:06.720 align:middle line:84%
Let's just assume for the
moment that the British banks

00:15:06.720 --> 00:15:10.970 align:middle line:84%
or political figures are shadowy
figures behind the scene, are

00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:14.460 align:middle line:84%
the dominant force in the
Federal Reserve System.

00:15:14.460 --> 00:15:16.030 align:middle line:90%
So what?

00:15:16.030 --> 00:15:18.140 align:middle line:84%
We still have to get
rid of it, you see?

00:15:18.140 --> 00:15:20.470 align:middle line:84%
We can talk about
who is behind that

00:15:20.470 --> 00:15:23.360 align:middle line:84%
and who is getting the most
benefit, but none of that

00:15:23.360 --> 00:15:24.240 align:middle line:90%
makes any difference.

00:15:24.240 --> 00:15:26.520 align:middle line:90%
We know it's not us.

00:15:26.520 --> 00:15:28.420 align:middle line:84%
So let's get on
with the real job

00:15:28.420 --> 00:15:30.320 align:middle line:90%
and get rid of this monster.

00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:32.600 align:middle line:90%
Let's slay this creature.

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:35.220 align:middle line:84%
Usually in that argument,
you find the idea

00:15:35.220 --> 00:15:38.690 align:middle line:84%
that, well, it's those big, bad
bankers that are the problem.

00:15:38.690 --> 00:15:40.730 align:middle line:84%
We're paying interest
on the national debt

00:15:40.730 --> 00:15:44.470 align:middle line:84%
to these big, bad bankers, and
interest on private debt, too.

00:15:44.470 --> 00:15:47.880 align:middle line:84%
So all we got to do is just get
those banker out of the picture

00:15:47.880 --> 00:15:51.460 align:middle line:84%
and turn this fiat money
system over to the treasury

00:15:51.460 --> 00:15:56.010 align:middle line:84%
and let the federal
government run the scam.

00:15:56.010 --> 00:15:57.500 align:middle line:90%
See?

00:15:57.500 --> 00:15:59.460 align:middle line:84%
We can't trust those
big, bad bankers,

00:15:59.460 --> 00:16:02.237 align:middle line:84%
but those nice, friendly,
trustworthy politicians

00:16:02.237 --> 00:16:02.820 align:middle line:90%
are different.

00:16:02.820 --> 00:16:05.450 align:middle line:84%
We can trust them to
take care of the problem.

00:16:05.450 --> 00:16:08.460 align:middle line:84%
This is the hidden message
behind that argument.

00:16:08.460 --> 00:16:09.670 align:middle line:90%
Let's see who's behind it.

00:16:09.670 --> 00:16:10.300 align:middle line:90%
And they're foreigners.

00:16:10.300 --> 00:16:11.883 align:middle line:84%
Well, we don't like
foreigners, right?

00:16:11.883 --> 00:16:14.110 align:middle line:84%
So let's get it back
to the people, which

00:16:14.110 --> 00:16:16.810 align:middle line:84%
means to the politicians
in Washington.

00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:19.340 align:middle line:84%
And I don't like
that solution at all.

00:16:19.340 --> 00:16:20.812 align:middle line:90%
I think it's a trap.

00:16:20.812 --> 00:16:23.270 align:middle line:84%
And I'm glad you brought it
up, because it gave me a chance

00:16:23.270 --> 00:16:25.880 align:middle line:90%
to express my views on that.

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:28.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: So I'm interested
in looking at the fact

00:16:28.070 --> 00:16:30.450 align:middle line:84%
that we have the
Federal Reserve that

00:16:30.450 --> 00:16:34.720 align:middle line:84%
gets started in 1913, in which
the American government quite

00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:37.550 align:middle line:84%
literally outsourced the
issuance of its currency

00:16:37.550 --> 00:16:41.260 align:middle line:84%
to a consortium of
private bankers.

00:16:41.260 --> 00:16:45.910 align:middle line:84%
And then within four years,
we have the conditions

00:16:45.910 --> 00:16:48.900 align:middle line:84%
that lead up to World
War I, including

00:16:48.900 --> 00:16:51.670 align:middle line:84%
the rise of the Russian
Revolution of 1917,

00:16:51.670 --> 00:16:54.120 align:middle line:90%
the Bolshevik Revolution.

00:16:54.120 --> 00:16:55.990 align:middle line:84%
Is that just a
coincidence, or is there

00:16:55.990 --> 00:17:00.490 align:middle line:84%
are some connective thread
between the foundation

00:17:00.490 --> 00:17:03.880 align:middle line:84%
the Federal Reserve and
the start of these wars?

00:17:03.880 --> 00:17:07.660 align:middle line:84%
In short, I guess what
I'm really asking is,

00:17:07.660 --> 00:17:11.140 align:middle line:84%
is there a reason for why a
banking cartel like the Federal

00:17:11.140 --> 00:17:13.220 align:middle line:84%
Reserve would want
there to be a war?

00:17:13.220 --> 00:17:15.050 align:middle line:90%
Do they profit off of it?

00:17:15.050 --> 00:17:17.210 align:middle line:84%
And if so, how are
they benefiting

00:17:17.210 --> 00:17:19.089 align:middle line:90%
from creating these wars?

00:17:19.089 --> 00:17:20.839 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: It's a
complex question

00:17:20.839 --> 00:17:23.430 align:middle line:90%
with different components to it.

00:17:23.430 --> 00:17:26.160 align:middle line:84%
First of all, Woodrow
Wilson was concerned,

00:17:26.160 --> 00:17:29.420 align:middle line:84%
as far as I can see
in his later years,

00:17:29.420 --> 00:17:33.330 align:middle line:84%
was concerned about this
creature, the Federal Reserve,

00:17:33.330 --> 00:17:35.565 align:middle line:84%
that he had helped
create, by the way.

00:17:35.565 --> 00:17:36.940 align:middle line:84%
I think it's
important for people

00:17:36.940 --> 00:17:41.020 align:middle line:84%
to know that Wilson himself was
a big supporter of the Federal

00:17:41.020 --> 00:17:41.520 align:middle line:90%
Reserve.

00:17:41.520 --> 00:17:46.800 align:middle line:84%
And without his cooperation and
behind-the-scenes endorsement,

00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:48.590 align:middle line:84%
the Federal Reserve
probably would never

00:17:48.590 --> 00:17:50.490 align:middle line:90%
have been enacted into law.

00:17:50.490 --> 00:17:52.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: Is that
just a coincidence?

00:17:52.210 --> 00:17:55.470 align:middle line:90%
Was war good business for them?

00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:59.870 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: So the issue is that
why are the bankers doing this?

00:17:59.870 --> 00:18:02.800 align:middle line:84%
Is it just because they
want to make money?

00:18:02.800 --> 00:18:06.560 align:middle line:84%
Or do they have political
objectives as well?

00:18:06.560 --> 00:18:09.990 align:middle line:84%
And if it's primarily
money, does war

00:18:09.990 --> 00:18:12.060 align:middle line:84%
help them achieve
that objective?

00:18:12.060 --> 00:18:14.120 align:middle line:90%
Duh, of course.

00:18:14.120 --> 00:18:19.040 align:middle line:84%
Nations at war spend
huge amounts of money,

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:20.880 align:middle line:84%
and they don't get
it from direct taxes.

00:18:20.880 --> 00:18:23.970 align:middle line:84%
They always get it
through inflation.

00:18:23.970 --> 00:18:27.725 align:middle line:84%
They always get it through their
central banks, who just create

00:18:27.725 --> 00:18:30.680 align:middle line:84%
it out of thin air,
pump it into the economy

00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:34.150 align:middle line:84%
through the government,
and it's inflation.

00:18:34.150 --> 00:18:37.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's why the price of
gasoline and bread and college

00:18:37.670 --> 00:18:40.660 align:middle line:84%
educations keeps
going up, up, up,

00:18:40.660 --> 00:18:43.250 align:middle line:84%
because the value of the dollar
keeps going down, down, down.

00:18:43.250 --> 00:18:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And that lost value is what is
siphoned off to the government

00:18:47.510 --> 00:18:49.990 align:middle line:90%
so they can fight the wars.

00:18:49.990 --> 00:18:52.040 align:middle line:84%
That's how they
finance the wars.

00:18:52.040 --> 00:18:55.100 align:middle line:84%
And we pay for it through
inflation primarily.

00:18:55.100 --> 00:19:00.530 align:middle line:84%
So sure, central banks
and, well, any bank

00:19:00.530 --> 00:19:02.600 align:middle line:90%
loves to make loans.

00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:04.210 align:middle line:90%
They're born to make loans.

00:19:04.210 --> 00:19:06.010 align:middle line:84%
That's how they
make their money.

00:19:06.010 --> 00:19:10.050 align:middle line:84%
And so there's no bigger
borrower than the government

00:19:10.050 --> 00:19:11.650 align:middle line:90%
fighting a war.

00:19:11.650 --> 00:19:14.270 align:middle line:84%
So it's just obvious once
you see the picture of that.

00:19:14.270 --> 00:19:17.020 align:middle line:84%
It is very much in the
interest of the Federal Reserve

00:19:17.020 --> 00:19:22.550 align:middle line:84%
and every other central bank
in the world to be the lender

00:19:22.550 --> 00:19:25.410 align:middle line:84%
to their governments
on a big scale.

00:19:25.410 --> 00:19:31.100 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing quite as big
a scale as a war for survival.

00:19:31.100 --> 00:19:33.800 align:middle line:84%
And under those conditions,
the politicians and the people

00:19:33.800 --> 00:19:35.987 align:middle line:84%
themselves don't ask
what the price tag is.

00:19:35.987 --> 00:19:38.070 align:middle line:84%
They don't say, how much
is this going to cost us?

00:19:38.070 --> 00:19:40.250 align:middle line:84%
They say, I don't care
what the price is.

00:19:40.250 --> 00:19:43.550 align:middle line:84%
We have to win the war,
or we'll be conquered.

00:19:43.550 --> 00:19:48.870 align:middle line:84%
So wars have always been a prime
weapon, a tool, if you will,

00:19:48.870 --> 00:19:50.460 align:middle line:90%
on the part of central banks.

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And in my mind at
least, David, if it

00:19:53.230 --> 00:19:55.250 align:middle line:84%
weren't for that
central bank mechanism,

00:19:55.250 --> 00:19:58.010 align:middle line:84%
where they could finance
wars in this easy fashion,

00:19:58.010 --> 00:20:02.210 align:middle line:84%
I think most modern wars
would never have been fought.

00:20:02.210 --> 00:20:03.950 align:middle line:84%
>>DAVID: In the
last year, we've now

00:20:03.950 --> 00:20:07.360 align:middle line:84%
heard about the LIBOR scandal,
where all the top banks that

00:20:07.360 --> 00:20:09.860 align:middle line:84%
are supposedly competing
with each other

00:20:09.860 --> 00:20:12.390 align:middle line:84%
are actually manipulating
their own interest

00:20:12.390 --> 00:20:15.220 align:middle line:90%
rates to benefit each other.

00:20:15.220 --> 00:20:16.620 align:middle line:90%
That's come out recently.

00:20:16.620 --> 00:20:19.532 align:middle line:84%
Would you say that
that's the smoking gun

00:20:19.532 --> 00:20:21.240 align:middle line:84%
that you've been
looking forward to prove

00:20:21.240 --> 00:20:23.155 align:middle line:84%
that this cartel
actually exists?

00:20:23.155 --> 00:20:24.530 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: Yes,
I think it's true

00:20:24.530 --> 00:20:29.030 align:middle line:84%
